        </div>
        <div class="text">
         <p>
          It‚Äôs hard not knowing whether the pain we are feeling is normal, just the result of using those muscles again to hold ourselves up, or is a sign of something wrong. I‚Äôve been considering calling my surgeon for another x-ray and checkup because sometimes my foot hurts so bad I‚Äôm SURE there‚Äôs got to be something wrong. But then it goes away for a while.
         </p>
         <p>
          To answer your questions, my balance is pretty good. Or at least as good as it was before, and clearly I was a klutz, so that‚Äôs not saying much! LOL. I don‚Äôt use crutches, a brace, or anything anymore, not on the trip either because I already had so much to lug around. I‚Äôm afraid to sell the crutches, though; I guess my crutches are a crutch, haha.
         </p>
         <p>
          I can‚Äôt jog but I can walk briskly, yes, once my ankle limbers up. Each time I get up from the computer or the couch or get out of the car, I‚Äôm starting from square one, it feels like, as far as stiffness goes. But after a couple of minutes, I can walk as though nothing ever happened. If I do it too long, I‚Äôll pay for it later, but for short distances, I do quite well. How about you? You‚Äôre a couple months behind me but you‚Äôre probably at that point where you‚Äôre starting to function normally again‚Ä¶?
         </p>
        </div>
